cs.LG, cs.CY, cs.CE, cs.HC, cs.DB 

Reasoning: 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper focuses on developing models to predict 24 hour discharge using Electronic Health Records (EHR) data. This involves applying machine learning techniques to the data, making cs.LG a likely sub-category. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society): The paper discusses the potential benefits of identifying patients who will be discharged within 24 hours, such as improving hospital resource management and quality of care. This falls under the broader category of computers and society, making cs.CY a possible sub-category. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper involves analyzing large amounts of EHR data to develop predictive models, which can be considered a form of computational engineering. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction): The paper discusses the potential impact of the predictive models on hospital resource management and quality of care, which involves human-computer interaction. 
- cs.DB (Databases): The paper uses EHR data to develop predictive models, which involves working with databases.
